title: WTB: T222's with good eye appeal...
author: Kzoo

posts.post_title: WTB: T222's with good eye appeal...
posts.post_content:
Guys.............Even though I only have about 10 so far, I'm looking to add to my collection of Fatima T222's. Although I'm not necessarily looking for technically high graded cards, I am looking for cards with good eye appeal and a dark image. Those are a must. Cards that would grade in the A-3 range are probably just fine. I don't care if a card is trimmed, off center, has a chipped corner, or a couple creases. Thanks and please PM me and I'll relay my email address for scans.

Matt

Hey Brian..........Thanks for posting your Fletcher. However, I'm looking for cards with more contrast, as many examples out there appear to be washed out, in my opinion. I want the dark areas 'black' and not 'grey'. When it comes to the contrast in the image, I'm a little anal about it. I'll post a few examples of mine later. Thanks for posting.............Matt
Here's some of my t222's and generally the condition and contrast of what I'm looking for. Thanks.......Matt
